BOOK ONE 23

“Whom, as the hart, his pasturage forsaking, Fleae when a wolf within the glade has stem, Thou, coward-like, shalt flee, all breathless, quaking— Boasts to thy love unkept.

“Achilles’ wrathful fleet may stay disaster A space from Phrygia's dames and llion's domes: Few winters yet and Danaan firae shall master The Pergamean homes.'’
